Black Leopards coach Cavin Johnson had a blocked artery on Friday and was rushed to hospital. JOHANNESBURG - Black Leopards coach Cavin Johnson was discharged from hospital after suffering a heart attack. Johnson, who's serving a suspension for what the club called poor performance, had a blocked artery on Friday and was rushed to hospital. His assistant at Leopards, Alan Clark, wished the 61-year-old well following the team's 2-1 success over Stellenbosh FC in an Absa Premiership clash. "My best wishes to coach Cavin," said Clark. "I just want him to know my thoughts and prayers are with him and his family and I wish him a speedy recovery."